@NODE Voraus " Requirement"

	@{b}MEAutoStart needs:@{ub}
	- OS 3.0+
	- the WBStart.library ((c) by Stefan Becker) (include)
	  in the Aminet under: util/libs/ 

	MEAutoStart only testet on a AMIGA 500 (OS3.0, 9MB Ram,
	68020, 520MD HD), but i think it run on all others Systems.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Einleitung " Introduction"

	MEAutoStart works like the AutoStart-function from Windo*s 95/98.
	But MEAutoStart can more:
	- For each Disk you can define, a script or program, which
	  will run if you insered, or remove.
	- You can disable the start from defined disks
	- It works with Disk, CDs, HDs,...
	- It is an Commodity with GUI

	You can define for each Volume his own Start-/Endfile set
	(@{"New Item" LINK "Eintrag"}, or on the volume is a standart
	file, the volume is scaned when the insert/removed volume
	not in the lists.

	@{b}These standartfiles are:@{ub}
	 @{b}Inserd:@{ub}
		MEAutoStart.Run: Start a program as workbench-prg.
		MEAutoStart.File: Start a Program as shell-prg.
		(If this file have a set S-Flag, the file will
		 also run)
	 @{b}Remove:@{ub}
		MEAutoEnde.Run: Start a Program as workbench-prg.
		MEAutoEnde.File: Start  Program as shell-prg.
		(If this file have a set S-Flag, the file will
		 also run)

	If the Endfile on the volume, the program will be copyed
	in the Tmp-Drawer (specifed in @{"Prefs" LINK "Prefs"}).

	@{b}The searchorder:@{ub}
		(1. Must i notify this device?) at this time : nu function
		2. Is the No-key pressd? -> No : End
		3. Is the Volume in the list? -> No : End Yes : Step 5
		4. Is the Volume marked? -> No : End Yes : Start
		5. Is a Startfile on the Volume? -> Yes : Start
	
		Start:
		 MEAutoStart start the File, and if there a endfile
		 specified it will be copied
		End:
		 MEAutoStart do nothing

	MEAutoStart have an AppIcon, when you drop a Volume into it,
	MEAutoStart search in the list this Volume, or lock on the
	volume for the MEAutoStart files, if MEAutoStart find some
	informationen MEAutoStart start the program.

	If you press the Not-Key (see @{"Prefs" LINK "Prefs"}, when you insert or remove
	an Volume, MEAutoStart will do nothing.

	@{b}NOTE:@{ub}
	If you do this a Endfile will also not kopied.

	The Listwindow is an AppWindow, you can drop a Volume into
	the window, and the Volume-startfile will be run. If you
	insert a file, a new item will be create.

		@{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub}
		MEAutoStart saves the lists normally only
	   	at the end of his life, if you have change the list
	   	it`s better to save the list from hand (with Menu
	   	->Edit->Save list)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Start " Start"

	The best way is, to install MEAutoStart in the WBStartUp
	drawer. 
	If there no parameter at a Shellstart the icon will be read.

	@{b}The parameter are:@{ub}
	 H=Hotkey "hotkey"
		commodity hotkey
	 P=Priority number
		commodity priority
	 P=Popup
		popup the window at the start
	 T=Tmp "tmp-drawer"
		the tmp-drawer
	 D=Drives "drives"
		the notify drives (No function at this time)
	 N=Not "not key"
		the key for disable the start (the list which
		keys you can use is @{"here" LINK "Nicht"}).

	At a WBstart the icon will be read.

	@{b}The tooltypes are:@{ub}
	 CX_HOTKEY="hotkey"
		commodity hotkey
	 CX_PRIORITY=number
		commodity priority
	 CX_POPUP=(YES|NO)
		popup the window at the start
	 TMP="tmp-drawer"
		the tmp-drawer
	 DRIVES="drives"
		the notify drives (No function at this time)
	 NOT="not key"
		the key for disable the start (the list which
		keys you can use is @{"here" LINK "Nicht"}).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Bedienung " Usage"

	PLEASE notice:
	Since Version 1.4 is there opnly one List, and if the item
	mark with a # on the begin of a line means this:

		mark:
			if this volume insert, MEAutoStart do something
		demark:
			if this volume insert, MEAutoStart do nothing

	In the mainwindow there is an list, which show all
	volumes, for there you have create an item.
	This items include the Start- and Endfile (with
	@{"NewItem" LINK "Eintrag"}).

	You can select the a item in the list with the mouse,
	(Mousewheel are supportet) and with the curosr-keys
	(Shift+cursor-key jump to the begin or the end of the
	list). All lists in MEAutoStart support this.

	@{b}The gadgets have this meaning:@{ub}
	- Start:
	   start the startfile from the selected item (but the
	   volume must be insert)
	- Yes<->No:
		mark/demark an item, where
		mark:
			if this volume insert MEAutoStart do something
		demark:
			if this volume insert MEAutoStart do nothing
	- Remove:
	   remove the selected item
	- New:
	   create a new volume item @{"New Item" LINK "Eintrag"}
	- Change:
	   change the volume item

	@{b}The menues have this meaning:@{ub}
	- The most are ready (I think so):
	- Prefs:
	   open the @{"Prefs-window" LINK "Prefs"}
	- Kill list:
	   remove the list.
	- Save list:
	   save the list

	If you press a define-Key, when you insert or remove
	an Volume, MEAutoStart will do nothing.

		@{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub}
		MEAutoStart saves the lists normally only
	   	at the end of his life, if you have change the list
	   	it`s better to save the list from hand (with Menu
	   	->Edit->Save list)
   	
@ENDNODE

@NODE Prefs " Prefs"

	The adjustment will be saved in the program icon.

	Hotkey, Priority, DoNotWait and PopUp are the standart
	Tooltypes for a commodity.

	@{b}The Gadgets:@{ub}
	- Device:
	 have no function at this time
	- Not:
		the key for disable the start (the list which
		keys you can use is @{"here" LINK "Nicht"}).

	The Gadgets Save, Use, Cancel do what they say.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Eintrag " New item"

	Here you can build up a Volume-item.

	@{b}The Gadgets:@{ub}
	- Volumes:
	   For which Volume is the item (you can select easy from the
	   insered volumes in the @{"Volumes windows" LINK "Volumes"})
	- Startfile:
	   File, which start, when you insert the Volume, specified
	   in the Volumegadget
	- Endfile:
	   File, which start, when you remove the Volume, specifies
	   in the Volumegadget

	You can choose the startmodus of the programs, as
	shell- or as workbench program.

	The menuitems clear, clears the Gadgets, the item copy
	double the item in the list.

	The window is an Appwindow, if drop a file into it will be
	insert in the startfilegadget.

	If you press the Help-Gadget in a stringgadget the Filerequester
	will pop up.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Nicht " Liste for Notkeys"

	The list shows all keys with which you can disable
	the start, choose one of it!

	@{b}You can choose:@{ub}
	- Left or Right Shift-Key
	- Left or Right Alt-Key
	- Left or Right Amiga-Key
	- Capslock-Key
	- ControlKey
	- Left, middle or right Mousebutton

	With a double-click on the list, or the Ok-Button,
	the selected item will be insert in the Eintrag-Window
	in the Volume-Gadget. With the Closewindow- or the
	Cancelgadget you can cancel the selection.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Volumes " Volumes"

	The list show all insert Volumes, with a double-click
	on the list, or the Ok-Button, the selected item will be
	insert in the Eintrag-Window in the Volume-Gadget.
	With the Closewindow- or the Cancelgadget you can
	cancel the selection.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Quickstart " Quickstart/Update"

	@{b}For people, who don`t gladly read Guides:@{ub}

	1. Close a running MEAutoStart
	2. Install the Program with the Installer
	3. Run MEAutoStart-Prefs out of the Installer
	4. Open the Prefs (Menu->Project->Prefs)
	5. Select the Drives which are notify from MEAutoStart
	6. Change the other items
	7. Save the Prefs
	8. Create new Volume-Item (with New Items)
	9. Close the Installer
	10. Ready

	If you Update MEAutoStart the old Icon in the WBStartup
	and the old Itemlists were preserve.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Version " Version/Future"

	@{b}Version 1.0 (10.01.1999):@{ub}
	 - The Program runs

	@{b}Version 1.1 (26.01.1999):@{ub}
	- The Guide is rewriten
	- The Install-Script is improved
	- A bug in the locale support is removed
	- You can now start from shell with parameters
	- You can use pattern (# and ?) in the Volumenames
	  (e.g. AMINET#?: All Aminet-CDs can handle with
	  one item)
	- If you press the LEFT Shift-Key, when you insert or remove
	  an Volume, MEAutoStart will do nothing.
	- Files that have set the S-Flag, the file will also run
	- MEAutoStart can cancel about the commodity-port

	@{b}Version 1.2 (07.02.1999):@{ub}
	- Sometime the About requester popt up, if you remove a Volume
	  -> this bug is removed
	- Improved Guide
	- You can choose the key, which cancel the start if you
	  insert/remove a Volume
	- The in the tmp-drawer copied file is delete after start
	- The in the tmp-drawer copied file has now a uniqe name
	- The bug in ethe GetVolume window is removed.
	- A simple Onlinehelp is build in
	- If you press the Help-Gadget in a stringgadget the Filerequester
	  will pop up (if there one)

	@{b}Version 1.3 (15.02.1999):@{ub}
	- The GUI is improved a bit
	- You can disable the start now with the left mosue button, too.
	- Sometimes a pufferd file wasn`t remove -> now it will remove.

	@{b}Verison 1.4 (20.05.1999):@{ub}
	- The Yes/Nolist are now one list, a converting tool to join
	  the both files is included
	- A tool for an easy registering is included

	@{b}Version 1.5 (01.06.1999):@{ub}
	- A bug in Registertool is removed
	- Some texts are reedit
	- Some Enforcer-Hits are removed
	- The online-help is now asynchron

	@{b}Future:@{ub}
	- Splitet in a prefs and a commodity-part
	- Support Shell- and ARexx-script
	- You can select the Devices that notify

@ENDNODE

